<main><section class="relative not-prose md:-mt-[76px] pt-10"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0" aria-hidden="true"></div><div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl relative px-4 sm:px-6"><div class="pointer-events-none md:pt-[76px] pt-4"></div><div class="pt-10 md:pT-16"><div class="mx-auto text-center max-w-5xl md:pb-4 pb-2"><p class="font-bold text-secondary tracking-wide uppercase text-base">Applied Research Services</p><h1 class="font-bold font-heading leading-tighter mb-4 md:text-6xl sm:text-5xl text-4xl tracking-tighter px-2 sm:px-0">Applied research solutions & Tangible projects</h1><div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-2 sm:px-0"><p class="text-muted mb-6 sm:text-xl text-lg">Sometimes, research finds.</p></div></div><div></div></div></div></section><section class="relative not-prose md:-mt-[76px]"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0" aria-hidden="true"></div><div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl relative px-4 sm:px-6"><div class="pointer-events-none md:pt-[76px] pt-0"></div><div class="lg:flex lg:gap-8 lg:h-screen lg:items-center lg:py-0 md:py-20 py-12"><div class="mx-auto px-2 sm:px-0 basis-1/2 lg:text-left md:pb-16 pb-10 text-center"><p class="font-bold text-secondary tracking-wide uppercase sm:text-base text-sm">Efficient AI Solutions</p><h1 class="font-bold font-heading leading-tighter mb-4 md:text-6xl sm:text-5xl text-4xl tracking-tighter">Symbolic AI with Formally Constrained Machine Learning</h1><div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl lg:max-w-none"><p class="text-muted mb-6 sm:text-xl text-lg">Integrating <span class="glitch-hover" data-text="formal systems">formal systems</span> with probabilistic inference engines to enable provably correct neural architectures. Our framework combines context dependent languages, curry-howard isomorphisms and a lot of types to constrain ML training within formally verified specifications. Applications include more efficient theorem proving, correct-by-construction code generation, and decidable constraint satisfaction to help decision-makers.</p><div class="flex flex-col gap-4 flex-nowrap lg:justify-start lg:m-0 lg:max-w-7xl m-auto max-w-xs sm:flex-row sm:justify-center sm:max-w-md"><div class="w-full flex sm:w-auto"><a class="w-full sm:mb-0 btn-primary" href="/contact">Research Collaboration</a></div><div class="w-full flex sm:w-auto"><a class="w-full sm:mb-0 btn-secondary" href="/dfs">DFS Laboratory</a></div></div></div></div><div class="basis-1/2"><div class="relative m-auto max-w-5xl"><img alt="ML Collaboration" class="w-full mx-auto bg-none rounded-lg xl:bg-transparent" src="/assets/images/product-hero.png" style="object-fit:cover;object-position:center;max-width:600px;max-height:600px;aspect-ratio:1;width:100%" decoding="async" height="600" loading="eager" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 400px, (max-width: 1023px) 768px, (max-width: 2039px) 1024px, 2040px" srcset="/assets/images/product-media-07.webp 400w, /assets/images/product.webp 600w, /assets/images/product-media-05.webp 768w, /assets/images/product-media-06.webp 1024w, /assets/images/product-hero.webp 1200w" width="600"></div></div></div></div></section><section class="relative not-prose md:-mt-[76px]"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0" aria-hidden="true"></div><div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl relative px-4 sm:px-6"><div class="pointer-events-none md:pt-[76px] pt-0"></div><div class="lg:flex lg:gap-8 lg:h-screen lg:items-center lg:py-0 md:py-20 py-12 lg:flex-row-reverse"><div class="mx-auto px-2 sm:px-0 basis-1/2 lg:text-left md:pb-16 pb-10 text-center"><p class="font-bold text-secondary tracking-wide uppercase sm:text-base text-sm">a sight of the productive future</p><h1 class="font-bold font-heading leading-tighter mb-4 md:text-6xl sm:text-5xl text-4xl tracking-tighter">Macroeconomics prediction Models</h1><div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl lg:max-w-none"><p class="text-muted mb-6 sm:text-xl text-lg">Applying learnt rules to create synthetic world models and help you see the edge of tommorow. Outlining social trends, long-term market behavior and probable collapses of overarching structures. Shaping a model to define the future.</p><div class="floating-quote mt-2"><div class="quote-ornament-mini">‹</div><blockquote class="quote-text-mini">Personne ne sait ce qu’il se passe aujourd’hui parce que personne ne veut qu’il se passe quelque-chose. En réalité on ne sait jamais ce qu’il se passe, on sait simplement ce qu’on veut qu’il se passe et c’est comme ça que les choses arrivent.</blockquote><div class="quote-attribution-mini"><span class="quote-author-mini">Marcus et Paul</span> <span class="quote-citation-mini">La naissance de L&#39;amour, Philippe Garrel</span></div></div></div></div><div class="basis-1/2"><div class="relative m-auto max-w-5xl"><img alt="Financial Analysis API" class="w-full mx-auto bg-none rounded-lg xl:bg-transparent" src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1691643158804-d3f02eb456a3?q=80&w=1974&auto=format&fit=crop&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D" style="object-fit:cover;object-position:center;max-width:600px;max-height:600px;aspect-ratio:1;width:100%" decoding="async" height="600" loading="eager" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 400px, (max-width: 1023px) 768px, (max-width: 2039px) 1024px, 2040px" srcset="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1691643158804-d3f02eb456a3?q=80&w=400&auto=format&fit=crop&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&h=400 400w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1691643158804-d3f02eb456a3?q=80&w=600&auto=format&fit=crop&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&h=600 600w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1691643158804-d3f02eb456a3?q=80&w=768&auto=format&fit=crop&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&h=768 768w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1691643158804-d3f02eb456a3?q=80&w=1024&auto=format&fit=crop&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&h=1024 1024w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1691643158804-d3f02eb456a3?q=80&w=1200&auto=format&fit=crop&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&h=1200 1200w" width="600"></div></div></div></div></section><section class="relative not-prose md:-mt-[76px]"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0" aria-hidden="true"></div><div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl relative px-4 sm:px-6"><div class="pointer-events-none md:pt-[76px] pt-0"></div><div class="lg:flex lg:gap-8 lg:h-screen lg:items-center lg:py-0 md:py-20 py-12"><div class="mx-auto px-2 sm:px-0 basis-1/2 lg:text-left md:pb-16 pb-10 text-center"><p class="font-bold text-secondary tracking-wide uppercase sm:text-base text-sm">Analog Neuromorphic Hardware</p><h1 class="font-bold font-heading leading-tighter mb-4 md:text-6xl sm:text-5xl text-4xl tracking-tighter">Interaction Net Processors for Biologically-Inspired Computation</h1><div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl lg:max-w-none"><p class="text-muted mb-6 sm:text-xl text-lg">Designing analog VLSI circuits that implement <span class="glitch-hover">interaction combinators</span> and symmetric interaction calculus at the hardware level. Our architecture enables massively parallel graph rewriting with constant-time β-reduction through asynchronous, event-driven computation. The happy fly™ project aims to simulate 10e16 Drosophila neurons (complete connectome) using interaction net substrates, achieving neuromorphic efficiency while maintaining <span class="pulse-subtle">formal correctness guarantees</span>.</p></div></div><div class="basis-1/2"><div class="relative m-auto max-w-5xl"><img alt="Analog Neuromorphic Processors" class="w-full mx-auto bg-none rounded-lg xl:bg-transparent" src="/assets/images/people.png" style="object-fit:cover;object-position:center;max-width:600px;max-height:600px;aspect-ratio:1;width:100%" decoding="async" height="600" loading="eager" sizes="(max-width: 767px) 400px, (max-width: 1023px) 768px, (max-width: 2039px) 1024px, 2040px" srcset="/assets/images/product-media-04.webp 400w, /assets/images/product-media-01.webp 600w, /assets/images/product-media-03.webp 768w, /assets/images/people.webp 1024w, /assets/images/product-media-02.webp 1200w" width="600"></div></div></div></div></section><div class="quote-block" data-astro-cid-xht55kip><div class="quote-ornament" data-astro-cid-xht55kip>‹‹</div><blockquote class="quote-text" data-astro-cid-xht55kip>Art is distinguished from Nature, as doing (facere) is distinguished from acting or working generally (agere), and as the product or result of the former is distinguished as work (opus) from the working (effectus) of the latter.</blockquote><div class="quote-attribution" data-astro-cid-xht55kip><span class="quote-author" data-astro-cid-xht55kip>E. Kant</span> <span class="quote-citation" data-astro-cid-xht55kip>Critique of Judgement</span></div><div class="quote-ornament quote-ornament-end" data-astro-cid-xht55kip>››</div></div></main>
